fr.enstb.xmlcode
Class KeyValueProperty

java.lang.Object
  fr.enstb.xmlcode.KeyValueProperty
Direct Known Subclasses:
ArrayKeyValueProperty, HashtableKeyValueProperty, SingleKeyValueProperty, VectorKeyValueProperty
public abstract class KeyValueProperty
extends java.lang.Object

A KeyValue property represents a property, accessible directly by related field or through accessors methods (get/set pair for single properties (see SingleKeyValueProperty), addTo../removeFrom.. pair for vector-like properties (see VectorKeyValueProperty), and set...ForKey/remove...WithKey for hashtable-like properties HashtableKeyValueProperty.

NB: to be valid, a KeyValueProperty object should be identified by at least the field or accessors methods.

Important note:If related field exist (is public) and accessors methods exists also, the operations are processed using accessors (field won't be used directly).

Author:
Sylvain Guerin
See Also:
KeyValueCoder, KeyValueDecoder
